#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""ticky: one-command setup of named, cross-platform subagents for a boss LLM.

Zero dependencies (Python stdlib only). One file. It is three things at once:
  1. a setup wizard      (ticky init / add / prefs / key / install)
  2. an MCP stdio server (ticky serve) exposing one tool per named agent
  3. a call logger        (ticky log) feeding the ticky widget (ticky widget)

The core (serve/init/add/log/call) is platform-neutral; everything that only
exists on one OS (the compiled status widget, launchd, Keychain probing) is
gated behind platform checks so the rest works anywhere Python does.

Config lives in ~/.ticky/config.json, secrets in ~/.ticky/env (0600),
call history in ~/.ticky/calls.jsonl, live state in ~/.ticky/state.json.
"""

